1
00:00:07,580 --> 00:00:10,300
♪Hush now, don't disturb
the moonlight on the pond♪

2
00:00:11,300 --> 00:00:14,260
♪A shattered heart
rests pillowed in my chest♪

3
00:00:15,020 --> 00:00:16,940
♪I would shield you♪

4
00:00:16,940 --> 00:00:19,940
♪From this cruel wind and frost♪

5
00:00:22,340 --> 00:00:24,820
♪The russet cloth
brushes against my heart♪

6
00:00:25,780 --> 00:00:28,620
♪Like sunset
draping over your shoulders♪

7
00:00:29,380 --> 00:00:30,940
♪This lingering afterglow♪

8
00:00:30,940 --> 00:00:34,780
♪Holds the image
of our very first glance♪

9
00:00:35,820 --> 00:00:39,460
♪I borrow a thousand-year wind
to caress your gauze window♪

10
00:00:39,820 --> 00:00:43,780
♪Tailoring moonlight
into your luminous gown♪

11
00:00:44,260 --> 00:00:50,180
♪Severing the past,
weaving a thousand yards of splendor♪

12
00:00:50,740 --> 00:00:54,340
♪With a thousand-year dream,
I seek the fragrance of your hair♪

13
00:00:54,580 --> 00:00:58,060
♪Pouring a lifetime of passion
into the silk you wear♪

14
00:00:59,020 --> 00:01:05,020
♪In this splendid world,
wherever you are is paradise♪

15
00:01:05,220 --> 00:01:11,700
=The Silk Master from the Future=

16
00:01:11,820 --> 00:01:16,700
=Episode 18=

17
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:20,960
My apologies,

18
00:01:21,520 --> 00:01:23,760
my lord. I've failed you.

19
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:46,160
Long Er,

20
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:49,000
what a spectacular performance.

21
00:01:51,040 --> 00:01:51,840
Get lost!

22
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:57,200
Useless piece of trash.

23
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:14,240
Careful.

24
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:16,560
Li Yunhe, how are you?

25
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:17,320
Are you alright?

26
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:18,400
Li Yunhe,

27
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:20,000
how are you feeling right now?

28
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:22,840
Li Yunhe, why do I have this feeling

29
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:23,960
that you're just faking it?

30
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:24,920
I...

31
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:28,840
I don't recall

32
00:02:28,840 --> 00:02:29,680
assigning you

33
00:02:29,680 --> 00:02:31,000
to any kind of cheerleading squad.

34
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:31,360
I...

35
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:32,920
You're supposed to be working,
not slacking off.

36
00:02:32,920 --> 00:02:33,920
What were you doing over there?

37
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:35,320
What are you still standing here for?

38
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:36,600
Get back to work, quick.

39
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:38,120
You're hurt.

40
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,520
I've got medicine right here.

41
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:41,960
This cures every ill under the sun.

42
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:43,120
Take it, quickly.

43
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:44,360
Take the medicine with your mouth,

44
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:45,160
not in your hand.

45
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:47,600
Oh, relax.

46
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:49,800
It's not poison. Just take it.

47
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:55,800
(What an absolute moron.)

48
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,200
(How can she be this clueless?)

49
00:02:57,920 --> 00:02:58,880
(Can't she see)

50
00:02:59,040 --> 00:03:00,400
(I'm trying to get her to leave?)

51
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:02,520
(She just had to pull this right now.)

52
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:05,400
Since Miss Zhao has gone to the trouble
of offering you medicine,

53
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:06,520
just take it.

54
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,400
What medicine do I need?

55
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:11,920
I was never even hurt.

56
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,480
- You aren't hurt?
- You're not injured?

57
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:15,520
I knew you were faking it.

58
00:03:15,640 --> 00:03:16,320
Li Yunhe,

59
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:17,760
you actually dared to deceive us?

60
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:18,920
No.

61
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:19,920
Let me weasel...

62
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:20,480
I mean,

63
00:03:20,481 --> 00:03:21,360
let me explain.

64
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,520
Things got urgent back there.

65
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:24,160
Long Er

66
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:25,600
absolutely had to lose.

67
00:03:25,720 --> 00:03:26,440
But the thing is,

68
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:28,320
the Marquis's heir
was right there watching.

69
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:29,520
If Long Er

70
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:30,720
had just lost outright,

71
00:03:31,040 --> 00:03:32,520
he'd be in serious trouble later.

72
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:33,320
So,

73
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:34,640
I had to pretend I was hurt too.

74
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:35,920
We were just giving each other an out.

75
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:37,040
It's basic courtesy.

76
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:38,160
You faked being hurt?

77
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:38,640
Why didn't you

78
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:39,720
tell us beforehand?

79
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:41,800
Li Yunhe, you really weren't hurt?

80
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:43,160
What a heartless man.

81
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:43,960
Ladies,

82
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:44,560
get him!

83
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:45,920
Wait!

84
00:03:46,040 --> 00:03:48,000
Mr. Li, I heard you were injured.

85
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:51,320
You all carry on.

86
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:52,040
Just carry on.

87
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:53,080
I didn't see a thing.

88
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:55,320
Miss Xue,

89
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:56,640
if there's

90
00:03:56,640 --> 00:03:57,800
something you need,

91
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:58,600
just say it.

92
00:03:59,320 --> 00:04:00,760
It's nothing, Mr. Li.

93
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:02,160
I only heard you had returned,

94
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:03,040
so I came by to check on you.

95
00:04:03,760 --> 00:04:04,920
My apologies.

96
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:06,240
I came at an awkward time.

97
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:07,200
I'm intruding.

98
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:07,840
Carry on.

99
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:08,920
I'll be on my way now.

100
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:09,320
No.

101
00:04:09,720 --> 00:04:11,320
You came at the perfect time.

102
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:13,400
I was just chatting with these ladies

103
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:14,560
about some things.

104
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:16,120
Nothing important.

105
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:17,720
Miss Xue,

106
00:04:17,720 --> 00:04:19,720
you're not injured either?

107
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:20,920
Xue Bingxiu,

108
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:22,720
what brings you here to Xianquan Tavern?

109
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:23,800
Naturally, it was Mr. Li

110
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,240
who arranged for me to recover here.

111
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:26,240
Miss Xue,

112
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:30,440
don't tell me you two have already...

113
00:04:32,520 --> 00:04:33,960
Mr. Li and I...

114
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:39,840
Miss Xue.

115
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:42,720
If there's something on your mind,

116
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:44,160
please just say it plainly.

117
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:47,480
Ladies, would you mind

118
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:48,960
giving us a moment alone?

119
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:50,520
Fine, I'll leave you to it.

120
00:04:50,520 --> 00:04:51,320
I'll go on ahead.

121
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:55,400
(I need to keep an eye)

122
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:56,320
(on Xue Bingxiu.)

123
00:04:56,320 --> 00:04:57,880
(I can't have her
whisking Li Yunhe away)

124
00:04:57,880 --> 00:04:59,280
(right under my nose.)

125
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:02,440
What are you still standing around for?

126
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:13,000
Miss Xue,

127
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,520
you can speak now.

128
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:16,080
Since you managed

129
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:17,640
to walk away
from a death trap this time,

130
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:19,000
I imagine it shouldn't be too hard
for you to guess

131
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:20,000
that I'm carrying

132
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:21,440
a few secrets with me.

133
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:22,800
I'm not particularly interested

134
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:24,560
in the secrets you carry.

135
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:26,240
Mr. Li, you may have no interest,

136
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:28,120
but that doesn't mean
others feel the same.

137
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:29,200
I must tell this secret

138
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:30,760
to you as soon as possible.

139
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:33,120
Fine.

140
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:34,720
Mr. Li,

141
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:37,320
I have yet to fully recover
from my severe injuries.

142
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:38,200
When I heard

143
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:39,720
you were hurt
in a life-or-death arena match,

144
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:40,760
I hurried over in a rush.

145
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:43,040
It must have aggravated my old wounds.

146
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:44,560
I feel

147
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:46,520
so very weak right now.

148
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:54,000
Well, if you're feeling weak,

149
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,480
how about I

150
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:57,520
give your shoulders a little rub?

151
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:01,320
Mr. Li,

152
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:03,960
I'm feeling so terribly weak right now.

153
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:06,040
Won't you put your arm around me?

154
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:07,640
I'm so afraid I might collapse.

155
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:09,840
Mr. Li...

156
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:16,120
What are you three

157
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:18,120
doing sneaking around out here?

158
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:21,240
I was just, uh...

159
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:23,400
Uh, I came back to grab something.

160
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:24,120
Where are my keys?

161
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:24,840
Let me look.

162
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:27,200
We were just worried you might be hurt.

163
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:28,520
Exactly.

164
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:30,520
A human life was at stake, after all.

165
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:32,520
Well, in that case,

166
00:06:32,720 --> 00:06:33,040
I suppose I should

167
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:34,160
thank you both for your concern.

168
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:35,240
You're welcome.

169
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:36,920
Li Yunhe,

170
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:37,960
how about

171
00:06:37,960 --> 00:06:39,640
you make a few extra dishes

172
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:44,200
to help replenish my kidneys?

173
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:45,320
My lower back

174
00:06:45,320 --> 00:06:46,520
has been feeling a bit off

175
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:48,120
these past couple of days.

176
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,520
Replenish your kidneys?

177
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:51,120
Since you're all already here,

178
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:52,320
come on out.

179
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:57,800
Yunhe,

180
00:06:58,720 --> 00:06:59,520
I was just...

181
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:01,840
Just passing through.

182
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:03,720
Passing through?

183
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:06,280
With two Shadow Guards in tow?

184
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:08,160
Makes perfect sense.

185
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:09,800
You're dismissed.

186
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:10,800
Understood.

187
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:15,600
Anyone else "passing through"?

188
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:22,560
You're all just unbelievable.

189
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:24,600
Miss Xue here already said
she didn't want this

190
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:25,920
to go beyond us.

191
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:27,440
A little open-mindedness, please.

192
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:27,920
Can't you give us

193
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:29,120
a little privacy?

194
00:07:29,960 --> 00:07:30,520
Oh,

195
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:32,000
my stomach is

196
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,520
suddenly feeling a bit off.

197
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:34,920
That's right.

198
00:07:34,920 --> 00:07:36,840
We ate something bad at lunch.

199
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:40,520
I'll take my leave then.

200
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:41,640
Goodbye.

201
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:43,520
Since you've come all this way,

202
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:44,760
why not stay a little longer?

203
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:46,960
Perhaps with more people here,

204
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:48,520
the risk Mr. Li has to shoulder

205
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:49,840
could be a bit less.

206
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:53,720
This is a secret letter

207
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:54,720
Chancellor Sun of this dynasty

208
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:55,920
left behind on his deathbed.

209
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:57,680
Chancellor Sun?

210
00:07:57,960 --> 00:08:00,120
The senior statesman
who served three emperors,

211
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:02,000
the teacher
of two generations of rulers?

212
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:04,720
When did he

213
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:06,320
pass away?

214
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:07,920
Not long ago.

215
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:09,800
He was murdered.

216
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:12,000
What...

217
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,920
What's inside this envelope?

218
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:15,120
The late emperor's final edict.

219
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:16,960
What?

220
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:20,200
The late emperor's final edict?

221
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:21,640
To be precise,

222
00:08:21,840 --> 00:08:23,560
it's not only a final edict
from the late emperor.

223
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:25,720
It also contains partial evidence

224
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:27,240
that Prince Ning has been

225
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:29,760
squeezing the people for tax silver
and raising an army over the years.

226
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:31,640
And who is Prince Ning?

227
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:34,040
Prince Ning is
the late emperor's younger brother,

228
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:36,120
the uncle of the reigning emperor.

229
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:38,720
Prince Ning harbors wild ambition...

230
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:39,520
Wait.

231
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:40,520
Hold on a second.

232
00:08:41,160 --> 00:08:42,800
Let me just get this straight.

233
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:44,240
First,

234
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:46,960
I was the Zhou live-in son-in-law.

235
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:48,200
Then,

236
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:49,160
I accidentally offended

237
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:50,720
the Marquis's heir.

238
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:51,920
And then,

239
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:53,440
I joined a poetry battle contest

240
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:54,720
at Chunfeng Pavilion.

241
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:56,040
And then,

242
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,400
for no reason at all,

243
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:58,920
I got dragged
into an imperial power struggle?

244
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:01,240
That just about sums it up.

245
00:09:01,920 --> 00:09:02,640
Sorry to barge in,

246
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:03,160
but I'll be going now.

247
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:04,120
Yunhe.

248
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:06,520
Since everyone is already here,

249
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:07,760
why don't we discuss this

250
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:09,760
and then decide whether to stay or go?

251
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:11,160
Yunzhuo,

252
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:13,200
what's the meaning of this?

253
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:14,640
Back off.

254
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:16,120
This is Feng City,

255
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:17,320
not the capital.

256
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:18,320
My life here

257
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:19,920
has just barely started looking up.

258
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:20,800
I really don't want

259
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:22,520
to lose my head for no good reason.

260
00:09:22,880 --> 00:09:24,080
You think there's no one

261
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:25,400
to put you in your place in Feng Cheng?

262
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:27,320
The Marquis House

263
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:29,160
has long been eyeing you
like a tiger watching its prey,

264
00:09:29,160 --> 00:09:30,400
ready to strike at any moment.

265
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:31,440
Besides,

266
00:09:31,920 --> 00:09:33,360
with the resources of the Marquis House,

267
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:35,440
finding out you saved Xue Bingxiu

268
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:37,760
and hid her here at Xianquan Tavern

269
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:39,400
is just a matter of time.

270
00:09:40,360 --> 00:09:41,360
The Marquis of Zhennan

271
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:43,400
has dealings with Prince Ning as well?

272
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:45,520
From the intelligence
I've gathered so far,

273
00:09:45,760 --> 00:09:47,440
the probability
of them conspiring together

274
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:49,520
is at least 80 percent.

275
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:50,920
Eighty percent?

276
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:52,920
So no matter which path you choose,

277
00:09:52,920 --> 00:09:54,240
whether Prince Ning takes you out

278
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:56,040
or the Marquis House deals with you,

279
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:58,360
there's not much difference
between the options.

280
00:09:58,520 --> 00:09:59,320
You really live up

281
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:00,520
to being my sworn brother, don't you?

282
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:02,440
You've pointed me down two paths,

283
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:04,600
each one leads straight to hell.

284
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:07,440
Yu, this has nothing to do with you.

285
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:08,080
You should go.

286
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,600
When the city gate catches fire,

287
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:10,720
the fish in the moat suffer.

288
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:13,120
When the Marquis House
starts settling scores,

289
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:14,560
the Zhou family
won't get to escape either.

290
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:15,920
I'm sorry, Yu.

291
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:17,600
I shouldn't have dragged you into this.

292
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:18,920
But don't worry,

293
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:20,520
even if I have to
give it everything I've got,

294
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:21,800
I will keep you safe.

295
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:23,320
I have a question.

296
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:24,640
Even if

297
00:10:24,640 --> 00:10:26,440
Prince Ning gets back
the late emperor's final edict,

298
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:28,240
there's already an emperor

299
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:29,840
sitting on the throne right now.

300
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:31,240
So,

301
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:33,200
shouldn't the late emperor's edict
in your hands

302
00:10:33,320 --> 00:10:34,800
be pretty meaningless by now, Miss Xue?

303
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:37,400
Chancellor Sun
thought the same way at first.

304
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:38,920
The emperor
had already ascended the throne.

305
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:39,920
Even if Prince Ning

306
00:10:39,920 --> 00:10:41,240
got hold of the late emperor's edict,

307
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:42,320
it wouldn't mean much.

308
00:10:42,760 --> 00:10:44,480
After all,
when the late emperor passed away,

309
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:46,280
Chancellor Sun had already

310
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:47,520
read the late emperor's
final edict aloud

311
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:49,120
before all the assembled officials.

312
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:51,520
Then where did this edict come from?

313
00:10:51,920 --> 00:10:52,520
This one

314
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:54,640
was given to Chancellor Sun
by Prince Ning.

315
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:55,880
What?

316
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,320
But the emperor
has already taken the throne.

317
00:10:58,440 --> 00:10:59,920
The late emperor's succession edict

318
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:01,240
must have already been used.

319
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:02,320
How could Prince Ning

320
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:04,320
possibly have
a late emperor's final edict

321
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:05,520
to give to Chancellor Sun?

322
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:07,400
What final edict
could Prince Ning possibly have?

323
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:10,520
This one is definitely a forgery.

324
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:11,960
It seems Prince Ning

325
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:14,320
is determined to rebel.

326
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:15,240
Li Yunhe,

327
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:16,640
don't go spouting nonsense.

328
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:17,760
If word like this gets out,

329
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:18,840
you'll lose your head.

330
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:20,320
I'm not spouting nonsense.

331
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:21,960
When the late emperor passed,

332
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:23,760
Chancellor Sun read the edict

333
00:11:23,760 --> 00:11:25,720
before the assembled ministers

334
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:27,840
and installed our current sovereign
on the throne.

335
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:29,520
Now, Prince Ning

336
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:31,520
can naturally just write one of his own

337
00:11:31,920 --> 00:11:32,600
and claim that the one

338
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:34,040
Chancellor Sun read aloud back then
was the fake,

339
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:35,800
and that his copy is the real one.

340
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:39,240
But this edict is a forgery.

341
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,440
If you were Prince Ning,

342
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:43,400
and you'd already steeled yourself
to rebel,

343
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:44,360
would you ever admit

344
00:11:44,360 --> 00:11:45,920
that your edict is a fake?

345
00:11:46,320 --> 00:11:47,520
If he really means to rebel,

346
00:11:47,760 --> 00:11:49,040
Prince Ning will definitely claim

347
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:49,960
that the reigning emperor's

348
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:51,240
succession edict is the false one,

349
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:53,040
accusing him
of seizing the throne illegitimately,

350
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:53,760
and that Prince Ning

351
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:54,840
is the true designated heir

352
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:56,560
chosen by the late emperor.

353
00:11:57,400 --> 00:11:58,520
But even if that's the case,

354
00:11:58,520 --> 00:11:59,560
it still doesn't explain

355
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:00,320
why Prince Ning

356
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:01,760
needs to get this edict back.

357
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:02,600
He could easily just

358
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:03,640
draft another one on his own.

359
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,400
Hold on a moment.

360
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:09,800
I'll just plug up my ears.

361
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,760
Carry on, you lot.

362
00:12:12,760 --> 00:12:13,880
This edict

363
00:12:14,120 --> 00:12:15,720
naturally has its own use.

364
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:18,280
Miss Xue.

365
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:20,240
I suppose you and Chancellor Sun

366
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:21,920
must have been quite close.

367
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:24,360
The fact that I was close
with Chancellor Sun

368
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:26,400
is known to many in the capital.

369
00:12:26,920 --> 00:12:27,800
In truth,

370
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:30,160
I'm Chancellor Sun's granddaughter.

371
00:12:34,640 --> 00:12:35,800
Chancellor Sun

372
00:12:36,160 --> 00:12:37,720
was a senior statesman of three reigns.

373
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:39,840
As his own granddaughter,

374
00:12:40,520 --> 00:12:41,920
how could you have fallen so far

375
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:42,800
to become a courtesan in Feng City?

376
00:12:43,920 --> 00:12:44,640
It seems

377
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:46,040
that on the very night

378
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:47,600
Chancellor Sun received this edict,

379
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:49,960
he was already murdered.

380
00:12:52,040 --> 00:12:53,120
How did you know that?

381
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:55,400
Are you one of Prince Ning's men?

382
00:12:58,520 --> 00:12:59,560
Why are you so surprised?

383
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:01,320
If I were one of Prince Ning's men,

384
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:02,320
would I have sunk so low

385
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:03,960
as to become
a live-in son-in-law for the Zhous?

386
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:05,320
If I were one of Prince Ning's men,

387
00:13:05,520 --> 00:13:07,040
I would've taught Lu Qifeng a lesson

388
00:13:07,360 --> 00:13:09,480
back at the gates of the Zhou Manor.

389
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:11,320
Prince Ning's power
overshadows the entire court.

390
00:13:11,320 --> 00:13:13,120
With your talents, if you followed him,

391
00:13:13,320 --> 00:13:13,960
you wouldn't

392
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:14,720
have to put up

393
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:16,400
with any more bull
from the Marquis House.

394
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:17,200
So...

395
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:18,640
So, how did you know

396
00:13:18,640 --> 00:13:19,200
that my grandfather

397
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,520
was killed right after receiving

398
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:21,440
this secret letter?

399
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:23,120
It's not that hard to guess.

400
00:13:23,640 --> 00:13:25,240
Perhaps,
from Chancellor Sun's perspective,

401
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:26,600
when Prince Ning had gotten his hands

402
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:28,040
on a forged imperial edict,

403
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:30,240
he was trying to force him
to pick a side.

404
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:31,600
So Chancellor Sun

405
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:33,120
not only refused Prince Ning

406
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:34,520
but was about to report him.

407
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:35,440
It's just a pity

408
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:36,880
that Chancellor Sun missed

409
00:13:36,880 --> 00:13:37,920
Prince Ning's cunning scheme.

410
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:40,640
The moment
he received that secret letter,

411
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:42,640
no matter which side he chose to take,

412
00:13:42,920 --> 00:13:43,960
he was destined to die.

413
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:46,040
So,

414
00:13:46,320 --> 00:13:48,920
Prince Ning
gave Chancellor Sun the edict

415
00:13:48,920 --> 00:13:50,240
not to win him over.

416
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:51,520
The way I see it,

417
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:52,720
Prince Ning simply wanted

418
00:13:52,720 --> 00:13:54,200
to use Chancellor Sun as a shield

419
00:13:54,720 --> 00:13:56,840
to whitewash
this fake late emperor's edict.

420
00:13:57,320 --> 00:13:57,880
Exactly.

421
00:13:58,280 --> 00:14:00,760
Chancellor Sun was the one designated

422
00:14:00,760 --> 00:14:02,440
to read the edict
when the late emperor passed away.

423
00:14:02,840 --> 00:14:04,040
When this edict

424
00:14:04,280 --> 00:14:05,760
got out from the Chancellor's Residence,

425
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:08,240
even though it's a fake,

426
00:14:08,800 --> 00:14:10,800
Prince Ning
would stand righteously and declare

427
00:14:10,800 --> 00:14:11,520
that it's genuine.

428
00:14:11,520 --> 00:14:13,400
I didn't hear a thing.

429
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,200
You're all correct.

430
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,400
In his final moments, my grandfather

431
00:14:16,720 --> 00:14:18,320
did indeed think of that,

432
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:19,920
which is why he repeatedly emphasized

433
00:14:19,920 --> 00:14:20,560
that this secret letter

434
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:22,400
must absolutely not fall into
Prince Ning's hands.

435
00:14:25,120 --> 00:14:26,960
Ugh, penny-wise, pound-foolish.

436
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:27,880
I never should've

437
00:14:27,880 --> 00:14:28,960
let that 500 taels of silver

438
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:30,840
lure me into that poetry battle contest
at Chunfeng Pavilion.

439
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:31,600
When it comes down to it,

440
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:33,440
it's because of you, you jinx.

441
00:14:33,440 --> 00:14:34,200
Whoever's tangled up with you,

442
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,360
it's pretty hard
to dodge the doomed ending.

443
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:38,800
Li Yunhe, you have to stay fine.
Don't die.

444
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:40,520
Don't worry.

445
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:42,320
When you hit a mountain,
there'll always be a path through.

446
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:43,440
Besides,

447
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:45,400
we've got the edict with us right now.

448
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:48,160
It's not yet clear who will win.

449
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:50,400
Mr. Li,
you truly have remarkable courage,

450
00:14:50,840 --> 00:14:52,920
nothing like the Prefect of Feng City.

451
00:14:54,160 --> 00:14:55,400
Once he learned of this matter,

452
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:57,360
he sent me out
of the Prefect's Office that very night,

453
00:14:57,920 --> 00:14:59,200
terrified of being caught up
in the karma of it all.

454
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:00,920
Isn't that stating the obvious?

455
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:01,840
What the Prefect did

456
00:15:02,040 --> 00:15:03,560
just goes to show he's

457
00:15:03,560 --> 00:15:04,520
an exceedingly shrewd man.

458
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:05,960
Whenever the throne changes hands,

459
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:07,160
whenever dynasties shift,

460
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:09,200
hasn't it always been
a blood-soaked hellscape?

461
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:10,520
Mr. Li,

462
00:15:10,760 --> 00:15:11,400
you and I

463
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:12,640
are now in the same boat.

464
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:13,480
We can only look up to

465
00:15:13,480 --> 00:15:14,960
your brilliant mind.

466
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:16,200
You must help me think of a way out.

467
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:17,000
Stop right there.

468
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:18,120
You're a walking catastrophe.

469
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:19,400
You've ruined us all.

470
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:20,640
What are you snarling for?

471
00:15:20,760 --> 00:15:21,600
You were the one

472
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:22,520
who first came after me

473
00:15:22,520 --> 00:15:23,800
when you won the poetry contest.

474
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:25,160
You've got some nerve saying that?

475
00:15:25,160 --> 00:15:26,320
If you hadn't been
running around everywhere

476
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:27,400
with this edict,

477
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:28,280
would all of us here

478
00:15:28,280 --> 00:15:29,960
have gotten tangled up in this with you?

479
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:30,920
If I hadn't run,

480
00:15:30,920 --> 00:15:31,920
should I have just waited

481
00:15:31,920 --> 00:15:33,400
for Prince Ning's men to kill me?

482
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:34,240
Prince Ning is plotting...

483
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:35,400
Enough. Stop it.

484
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:38,120
Alright now.

485
00:15:38,440 --> 00:15:39,080
Since

486
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:40,440
we're all dragged into this together,

487
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:42,320
let's each put forward our thoughts

488
00:15:42,320 --> 00:15:43,320
and come up with a plan.

489
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:49,120
What?

490
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:51,160
What are you all looking at me for?

491
00:15:51,920 --> 00:15:53,520
I'm just a measly

492
00:15:54,280 --> 00:15:55,640
cast-off nobody.

493
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:57,120
I don't have any ideas.

494
00:15:57,920 --> 00:15:58,720
The most pressing matter

495
00:15:58,720 --> 00:15:59,760
is to get this information

496
00:15:59,880 --> 00:16:01,120
to His Majesty immediately.

497
00:16:01,160 --> 00:16:02,160
Right now, Prince Ning already

498
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:03,840
wields power
that eclipses the entire court.

499
00:16:05,160 --> 00:16:06,320
That means

500
00:16:06,560 --> 00:16:07,560
the current sovereign

501
00:16:07,680 --> 00:16:09,120
is nothing more than a puppet.

502
00:16:43,100 --> 00:16:46,700
♪Fine rain falls outside the pavilion♪

503
00:16:46,860 --> 00:16:50,060
♪With honors won, an old friend returns♪

504
00:16:50,580 --> 00:16:53,300
♪Who took the March rain♪

505
00:16:53,540 --> 00:16:56,900
♪To dye the silk against the skin♪

506
00:16:57,260 --> 00:17:00,060
♪Yam juice enriches the silk threads♪

507
00:17:00,220 --> 00:17:03,420
♪Weaving the Milky Way
down to the mortal world♪

508
00:17:04,300 --> 00:17:10,220
♪Needle and thread
stitch away the marks of time♪

509
00:17:10,260 --> 00:17:13,700
♪Cutting a yard of the misty rain♪

510
00:17:13,940 --> 00:17:16,780
♪Embroidering half a scroll
of earthly verses♪

511
00:17:16,940 --> 00:17:19,220
♪Where the golden honors hang high♪

512
00:17:19,220 --> 00:17:23,420
♪The clouds dance in the air♪

513
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:26,780
♪Brewing wine, we speak of legends♪

514
00:17:26,940 --> 00:17:30,060
♪In fine liquor,
true feelings are revealed♪

515
00:17:30,580 --> 00:17:33,500
♪In this life I'd be a cloud-tailor♪

516
00:17:33,660 --> 00:17:40,180
♪Never failing the stars,
nor failing you♪

517
00:18:06,460 --> 00:18:09,980
♪Fine rain falls outside the pavilion♪

518
00:18:10,220 --> 00:18:13,380
♪With honors won, an old friend returns♪

519
00:18:13,980 --> 00:18:16,700
♪Who took the March rain♪

520
00:18:16,900 --> 00:18:20,220
♪To dye the silk against the skin♪

521
00:18:20,620 --> 00:18:23,500
♪Yam juice enriches the silk threads♪

522
00:18:23,580 --> 00:18:27,300
♪Weaving the Milky Way
down to the mortal world♪

523
00:18:27,340 --> 00:18:30,620
♪Warp and weft entwine,
one shuttle, one dream♪

524
00:18:30,620 --> 00:18:33,580
♪As seasons change♪

525
00:18:33,580 --> 00:18:37,220
♪Cutting a yard of the misty rain♪

526
00:18:37,220 --> 00:18:40,060
♪Embroidering half a scroll
of earthly verses♪

527
00:18:40,140 --> 00:18:42,700
♪Where the golden honors hang high♪

528
00:18:42,700 --> 00:18:46,780
♪The clouds dance in the air♪

529
00:18:46,780 --> 00:18:50,100
♪Brewing wine, we speak of legends♪

530
00:18:50,100 --> 00:18:53,820
♪In fine liquor,
true feelings are revealed♪

531
00:18:54,220 --> 00:18:57,340
♪Washing away
a lifetime of wear and tear♪

532
00:18:57,340 --> 00:19:00,220
♪Only for you♪

533
00:19:00,220 --> 00:19:03,820
♪On the street of golden honors,
the music rises♪

534
00:19:03,940 --> 00:19:06,700
♪The moon moves west
beyond the pavilion♪

535
00:19:06,820 --> 00:19:09,380
♪Wine runs dry, yet the revelry lingers♪

536
00:19:09,380 --> 00:19:13,460
♪In silk, I seek a kindred soul♪

537
00:19:13,460 --> 00:19:16,780
♪The rain has ceased,
clouds begin to clear♪

538
00:19:16,820 --> 00:19:20,180
♪The fragrant silk billows
under the low-hung stars♪

539
00:19:21,020 --> 00:19:26,700
♪I'd cut the clouds and morning glow
to drape over you♪

540
00:19:27,780 --> 00:19:31,900
♪A single bolt of silk becomes♪

541
00:19:33,180 --> 00:19:37,700
♪Your wedding gown♪
